### Create a new demo

To create a brand new demo, you can create a new net demo using Lancey’s chrome extension or you can choose to clone a demo based on what one of your team members have created.

For the purpose of this guide, we’ll focus on cloning existing demos as we can speed up the process.

Within the Lancey dashboard, you’ll notice there are demos that are already created by your team. Let’s learn to clone one.

1. Find a demo you want to clone    
2. Click on the demo name head to the demo editor
3. Once you’ve opened up a demo, click on **Copy demo** button to create a copy for your own use case    
4. Once your demo is cloned, make sure to navigate to the new demo so you don’t modify someone else’s by mistake!

## Publishing a demo

All demos created in Lancey get saved automatically but don't get published until you publish them. This is important because it allows you to continue making tweaks and updates without impacting what demo viewers see.

### Publishing options

When you have pending changes to publish, you'll need an alert in the top right bar next to the Preview button.

- You can open the **Publish** menu by click on the button.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f023b31bcd14df2c4080/file-KQAwbdUgif.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f023b31bcd14df2c4080/file-KQAwbdUgif.png)

- You'll get to see when the demo was last published (or if you've never published it previously).
- Hit the Publish button to make the demo public. This means everyone with the link to this demo can view it.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f071bfe3f971fb093b6f/file-vIFRicK8Qc.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f071bfe3f971fb093b6f/file-vIFRicK8Qc.png)

## Sharing options

You can access the Share menu by clicking on the **Share button** on top right bar.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f145b31bcd14df2c4086/file-HfmKQPdMRM.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f145b31bcd14df2c4086/file-HfmKQPdMRM.png)

You have several options when it comes to sharing your demos with viewers.

### Normal links

This is a great option when you want to share your demo through a link whether to a group or individuals.

You have a few options when you generate a link, including:

- Naming the link for tracking purposes
- Setting expiry
- Passcode

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f226f6d1fb09b86ce6dc/file-4op8riyH8x.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f226f6d1fb09b86ce6dc/file-4op8riyH8x.png)

### Embed link

By using embed link, you can insert the demo onto your website for your visitors to try out. After you create an embed link, you'll receive a block of code to copy directly on your website.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f360bfe3f971fb093b72/file-ComZHU5EXB.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f360bfe3f971fb093b72/file-ComZHU5EXB.png)

### Mail merge links

Mail merge links allow you to use a single link and track engagement uniquely for each recipient, which is great when you’re sending cold emails and want to leverage demos as part of it. These are great for adding into your sales engagement platform such as Apollo, Salesloft, and Outreach.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f3d2d0b6de7e3be2a595/file-JLgutvZCpB.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f3d2d0b6de7e3be2a595/file-JLgutvZCpB.png)

Once you create a mail merge link, you'll see an extra parameter being added to the link which will get merged from the sales engagement platform. In example below, {{email}} will be provided by Outreach so we can uniquely track our demo analytics per receipt of the sequence.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f449f6d1fb09b86ce6de/file-XfoHkeqSeV.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b5f449f6d1fb09b86ce6de/file-XfoHkeqSeV.png)

## Editing and sharing your demo

Demo editing allows you to control where the hotspots and tooltips get rendered on your demo. This is useful because it allows you to control what users see and the order they see it in.

In the example blow, the text inside the **orange box** is the **Tooltip text** and **black outlined box** is the **Hotspot**.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b47f47b31bcd14df2c3ee8/file-JgwxtV73nx.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b47f47b31bcd14df2c3ee8/file-JgwxtV73nx.png)

### Creating new hotspots

Every time you create a demo, Lancey will create a Hotspot based on where you clicked, typed, or interacted with the application. This makes it a breeze to easily launch new demos.

If you want to create a new hotspot

- **Select a new element** (indicated by the red border) on a frame
- Click on the **Set hotspot** button

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63c1c24ed0b6de7e3be2af29/file-xD74dzJaY8.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63c1c24ed0b6de7e3be2af29/file-xD74dzJaY8.png)

- A Hotspot settings menu will open with few options. You can update the **title**, **message** (the text displayed in the tooltip) and **placement** of this hotspot.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4843ca199b514924d92fd/file-7SLKRvobtF.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4843ca199b514924d92fd/file-7SLKRvobtF.png)

- You can also toggle Focus mode on the hotspot to darken the background or add a call to action when the user sees the hotspot (similar to the Contact us button below).

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4cd5ba199b514924d9352/file-OHZkuU0ulr.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4cd5ba199b514924d9352/file-OHZkuU0ulr.png)

### Editing tooltips text

- To edit an existing hotspot's tooltip, open up the Hotspot settings menu from the top bar.

![https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4cd96bfe3f971fb093a3e/file-A11td6SFUo.png](https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/63a0bb4c1e9b0d75c72746e6/images/63b4cd96bfe3f971fb093a3e/file-A11td6SFUo.png)

- A Hotspot settings menu will open with few options. You can update the **title**, **message** (the text displayed in the tooltip) and **placement** of this hotspot.

